 :tx/rationale "ONLINE-RETEST RESULT: 4.1/10. Online calibration WORKED (threshold calibrated to 0.57 from 0.20 after 10 observations). BUT concept collapse persists because multi-membership still assigns to ALL concepts. The issue: model2vec cosine similarities between observations and innate concepts are tightly clustered (range 0.15-0.68). Even at threshold 0.57, the sigmoid soft membership gives non-trivial strength to concepts with cosine 0.30-0.50. The ACTUAL fix needed: top-K assignment, not threshold-based. Instead of 'assign to all concepts above threshold', use 'assign to the K concepts with highest similarity, where K is determined by the gap between the best and worst matches'. If best_sim - worst_sim > 0.3, assign only to top 1-2 concepts. If the gap is small (all concepts equally relevant), assign to all (the current behavior). This is a MAX-GAP heuristic that naturally adapts to the similarity distribution. Traces to: ADR-FOUNDATION-031, INV-EMBEDDING-004."
